node.text: 😸Have you faced the legendary opponents on Champion Island yet? We worked with Japanese animation studio STUDIO4C 🇯🇵 to create our largest interactive #GoogleDoodle ever. Go #BehindTheDoodle to learn more about the Doodle Champion Island Games and the ancient folklore that inspired it.

node.title: Behind the Doodle: Champion Island Games

Can you guess this pitmaster’s secret ingredient for smoking the best barbecue in town? 👀

It’s his Google Pixel. 

Learn more about Matt’s True Pixel Story and watch how his Pixel and Nest products have helped him run his business for the past eight years. #TrueStories

node.title: The Secret Ingredient - Matt’s True Pixel Story

node.text: In celebration of #Juneteenth, Local Guide @theAprilHamm is visiting historic places in New Orleans — like Congo Square and the Free People of Color Museum — and adding information about them to the map to make history more accessible. Her contributions show that being a Local Guide on @googlemaps is more than leaving reviews — it’s a way to share and commemorate history.

node.title: Preserving Black History on Google Maps

node.text: Fred Armisen (@sordociego) and fellow drummer Jason Barnes (@cybrnetx) first met while playing a show in 2019. Since then, Jason and a team of researchers finished development of a revolutionary TensorFlow-powered prosthetic drumming arm. Watch Jason demonstrate the capabilities of his new prosthetic as the two drummers reconnect and play together. 🥁

node.title: Forward Rhythm | Two Drummers with Fred Armisen and Jason Barnes

node.text:
“Playing music is the best feeling in the world. As long as I can do that, I’ll be happy.” — Jason Barnes

Jason Barnes (@cybrnetx), a drummer and composer from Atlanta, lost his lower right arm after an electrical accident in 2012. Determined to continue pursuing music, Jason worked with a group of Georgia Tech researchers to create a custom, TensorFlow-powered drumming arm that lets him drum almost as naturally as with his own arm.

node.accessibility_caption: White hand touching a new white Nest Doorbell.

node.text:
Available now: security with smarts from the new battery-operated #NestDoorbell and #NestCam.

Both Nest Cam and Nest Doorbell have intelligent alerts that only notify you about things that matter most. The new Nest Cams can recognize people, cars, animals and even packages on the new Nest Doorbell, and send you alerts when these things are outside or around your home.

Order the new Nest Cam and Nest Doorbell now at the link in bio.

node.text:
In honor of #NationalHoneybeeDay, meet the team using TensorFlow — Google’s open-source machine learning framework — to help save the world’s bees. 🐝 

We originally shared this story in 2019, but the lessons and the urgency of the mission are just as relevant today. Buzz on over to the link in bio to learn more.

node.text:
Introducing the budget-friendly Pixel 5a with 5G 👋

🎮 Play games 
📹 Take amazing video
🎬 Watch HD movies 
🔋 Power all day*
🔒 Keep your stuff secure

Available exclusively in the 🇺🇲 and 🇯🇵 . Learn more at the link in bio.

*Up to 18W wired charging rates are based upon use of the included charger plugged into a wall outlet. Actual results may be slower. Maximum battery life based on testing using a mix of talk, data, standby, and use of other features. Battery life depends upon many factors and usage of certain features will decrease battery life. Pixel 5a battery testing conducted by a third party in California in early 2021 on pre-production hardware and software, using default settings. Testing conducted on two major carrier networks using Sub-6 GHz non-standalone 5G (ENDC) connectivity. Actual battery life may be lower. 

Requires a 5G data plan (sold separately). 5G service is carrier dependent. Contact carrier for details. g.co/pixel/networkinfo for info.

node.text:
AR in Search lets you see your favorite athletes kick, hit, swim and flip… right in your living room. To bring this experience to life, we used a lightstage equipped with over 200 24-megapixel cameras to capture each athlete's likeness, and we used motion capture to record their real movements. We then used state-of-the-art compression to make these models, textures and animations smartphone-ready.

In this behind-the-scenes video, get an inside look at our “scan van” and hear from @caelebdressel, @mrapinoe and @simonebiles as they share their experiences being captured in AR. See their moves up close by searching one of their names in the Google app and then tapping on “View in 3D.”

node.text: In the latest episode of #ArtZoom from @GoogleArtsCulture, @JoeyKing, star of @NetflixFilm’s The Kissing Booth, discusses Gustav Klimt’s The Kiss — ASMR-style. 💋 Head to @GoogleArtsCulture for the full spine-tingling video, and check out @belvederemuseum for more of Klimt’s work.

node.accessibility_caption: Lucky the animated calico cat, from the Google Doodle Island Championship Games.

node.text: Over the last two weeks, Lucky, a brave calico (c)athlete, has explored a world of legendary quests and sports in our interactive #GoogleDoodle, the Doodle Champion Island Games. Head to our homepage to help Lucky defeat the island’s Champions and compete on the global leaderboard. Not ready to say goodbye to the competition yet? #ChampionIslandGames will be back soon 😺.

node.text:
👋 Meet the new battery-powered #NestCam and #NestDoorbell from Google: the extra set of eyes you want for your home.

📱Customize your alerts so you only get notifications about the things that matter most.
🕕 Monitor your home 24/7 from wherever you are with a live camera view.
🎨 Designed to fit in with your home decor since Nest Doorbell comes in a range of colors to suit your style.

Keep track of what’s happening around your home from anywhere with Nest Cam and Nest Doorbell. Tap the link in bio or visit googlestore.com to learn more.
